WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:05.240
(FIRE SIZZLES)
(ANIMAL SQUAWKS)

00:05.240 --> 00:08.840
(MYSTERIOUS MUSIC)

00:08.840 --> 00:10.760
MAN: To the south,
there were bushfires.

00:10.760 --> 00:12.040
To the west, there were bushfires.

00:12.040 --> 00:13.720
In every direction,
roads were cut off...

00:13.720 --> 00:16.840
WOMAN: ..and labelled the worst
fire season ever recorded.

00:16.840 --> 00:18.400
The country is burning.

00:18.400 --> 00:20.240
WOMAN: More than $55 million

00:20.240 --> 00:21.480
has been raised

00:21.480 --> 00:23.080
for the rural
fire service.

00:23.080 --> 00:25.000
(SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

00:25.000 --> 00:27.800
WOMAN: More than one billion animals
that have been killed as a result.

00:27.800 --> 00:31.280
WOMAN: Military helicopters
and fixed-wing aircraft

00:31.280 --> 00:34.640
are being prepared for bushfire
evacuations in the state.

00:34.640 --> 00:37.640
MAN: It's like a war zone.
Everything's just gone.

00:43.680 --> 00:46.720
(HEAVY BREATHING)

00:50.600 --> 00:53.680
This is an emergency warning
for Kooryang Point

00:53.680 --> 00:56.320
and surrounding areas.

00:56.320 --> 00:59.520
There is a bushfire to the west
that is out of control,

00:59.520 --> 01:02.600
and with the current wind direction
is moving towards town.

01:02.600 --> 01:05.520
(HUBBUB)

01:11.320 --> 01:15.880
The main road remains closed
and there is now no way in or out.

01:15.880 --> 01:20.160
Assembly areas are established
at the wharf and beach.

01:20.160 --> 01:22.760
Move to the beach or the wharf.

01:22.760 --> 01:26.360
Foot traffic only
and vehicles park over here.

01:26.360 --> 01:27.800
(INDISTINCT RADIO COMMUNICATION)

01:27.800 --> 01:30.800
No need to panic, but keep moving.

01:33.080 --> 01:34.360
(SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

01:38.200 --> 01:42.000
You are in danger
and need to act immediately

01:42.000 --> 01:43.800
in order to survive.

01:45.200 --> 01:47.320
It is too late to leave.

01:50.000 --> 01:52.560
MAN ON MEGAPHONE: Tourists,
if you don't know where to go,

01:52.560 --> 01:54.280
follow the path to the wharf.

01:54.280 --> 01:57.800
(SPEAK FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

02:00.320 --> 02:03.440
ADUT: Arrgh!
MAN ON MEGAPHONE: Keep going.

02:03.440 --> 02:05.320
Keep moving.

02:05.320 --> 02:08.520
Proceed to either
the beach or the wharf.

02:08.520 --> 02:12.080
Baba! Mama!
Keep going. Keep moving.

02:12.080 --> 02:14.760
Proceed to either
the beach or the wharf.

02:14.760 --> 02:16.400
(HUBBUB CONTINUES)

02:16.400 --> 02:20.240
Keep going. Keep moving.

02:20.240 --> 02:23.200
Proceed to either
the beach or the wharf.

02:28.800 --> 02:30.280
Baba!

02:41.400 --> 02:43.080
Baba?

02:49.000 --> 02:50.880
WOMAN ON RADIO: It's looking
pretty bad up here.

02:50.880 --> 02:53.200
I can see the actual front
approaching.

02:53.200 --> 02:56.360
It's maybe 20, 30km away.

02:56.360 --> 02:58.040
Moving pretty damn fast.

02:58.040 --> 03:02.520
Well, thank you for the call
and you stay safe.

03:02.520 --> 03:07.520
That information is for anyone still
in the vicinity of Dulverton Ridge.

03:07.520 --> 03:11.760
Fire is approaching.
Shelter in place.

03:11.760 --> 03:15.240
It's 8:21am, December 31.

03:15.240 --> 03:17.600
Not quite the New Year's Eve
anyone was planning.

03:17.600 --> 03:20.480
Certainly not what I had in mind.

03:20.480 --> 03:23.560
But you play the hand
you're dealt, don't you?

03:23.560 --> 03:25.880
I'm Caris Mazzeo.

03:25.880 --> 03:28.120
This is your community station.

03:28.120 --> 03:30.200
Stay tuned
for the latest information

03:30.200 --> 03:33.720
in this unfolding emergency.

03:35.080 --> 03:36.480
(DISTANT RUMBLING)

03:37.480 --> 03:38.880
(GENTLE MUSIC PLAYS)

03:38.880 --> 03:43.920
This is a song that my husband,
Bruno, used to play

03:43.920 --> 03:45.640
when he wanted to relax.

03:45.640 --> 03:48.000
And we could all do with that
right now, couldn't we?

03:50.240 --> 03:52.120
This is for you, my love.

03:54.280 --> 03:56.640
SONG: # Evie

03:59.240 --> 04:03.160
# There seems so much to say... #

04:03.160 --> 04:05.040
WOMAN: Adut!
MAN: Adut!

04:05.040 --> 04:06.920
ALEK: I'm tired. Where are we going?

04:06.920 --> 04:08.600
Adut!
I'm tired.

04:08.600 --> 04:10.000
Where are we going?
Stop it!

04:10.000 --> 04:12.120
We're looking for your sister. Adut!
Adut! Adut!

04:12.120 --> 04:13.760
I think I remember that fence.

04:13.760 --> 04:15.320
(SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

04:16.320 --> 04:17.480
MAN: Excuse me.

04:17.480 --> 04:20.680
I told you three days ago, Madit.
We should've gone home.

04:20.680 --> 04:22.560
(BOTH SPEAK FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

04:24.440 --> 04:27.760
I will find Adut
and I will meet you there.

04:27.760 --> 04:29.880
No. We stay together.

04:29.880 --> 04:31.720
We'll look for her together.

04:31.720 --> 04:34.040
(SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

04:41.520 --> 04:42.680
('EVIE PART 2' CONTINUES)

04:42.680 --> 04:44.280
Paddy, I know it's hell
for everybody,

04:44.280 --> 04:47.480
but I have barely had a breath of
fresh air for a day and a half.

04:47.480 --> 04:48.880
I didn't bring a toothbrush

04:48.880 --> 04:52.280
and the inside of my mouth
feels like a shag pile right now.

04:52.280 --> 04:56.840
So if you can't come, can you please
get someone else to relieve me?

04:56.840 --> 04:57.880
Please.

04:57.880 --> 05:02.840
# I wanna thank you now

05:03.960 --> 05:06.480
# For giving me this... #

05:08.200 --> 05:10.240
Boss. Hey?

05:10.240 --> 05:12.040
That's all your food.

05:14.080 --> 05:16.280
Hey!

05:16.280 --> 05:18.960
Dickhead! Drop it!

05:18.960 --> 05:20.320
That's my stuff!

05:20.320 --> 05:22.640
Uhh!
Hey!

05:22.640 --> 05:24.160
Shit!

05:24.160 --> 05:26.080
(MUTTERS)

05:26.080 --> 05:28.200
Kid! Hey.

05:28.200 --> 05:30.400
What the hell are you doing?

05:31.960 --> 05:33.680
Look. Come here.

05:34.880 --> 05:37.480
Up you get. You're right.

05:37.480 --> 05:39.120
There you go, no dramas.

05:39.120 --> 05:40.760
Tough kid.

05:43.640 --> 05:45.360
These your towels?

05:45.360 --> 05:47.880
Got 'em? Off you go.

05:47.880 --> 05:49.080
But...
What?

05:49.080 --> 05:50.480
..I don't know where to go.

05:50.480 --> 05:53.800
I lost my parents
and now I can't find them.

05:53.800 --> 05:56.160
I need a phone.
What?

05:56.160 --> 05:57.800
Have you got a phone?

05:59.040 --> 06:01.360
OK. Dammit.

06:01.360 --> 06:04.040
Here. Give me those. Here you go.

06:04.040 --> 06:06.000
Call them.
You know how to use that?

06:06.000 --> 06:08.320
It's not working.
Yes, it is.

06:08.320 --> 06:10.680
Press the numbers.

06:10.680 --> 06:12.160
Shit.

06:14.000 --> 06:15.200
(SOFTLY) Fuck.

06:15.200 --> 06:16.680
The tower's out.

06:16.680 --> 06:19.440
Um, OK.

06:19.440 --> 06:21.520
Alright, so what do they look like?

06:21.520 --> 06:24.560
They're tall and black.

06:24.560 --> 06:25.640
Like me.

06:25.640 --> 06:28.480
Come on, kid.

06:30.120 --> 06:32.840
Fuck. I can give you
five minutes, OK?

06:32.840 --> 06:34.600
10 minutes tops.

06:34.600 --> 06:38.160
I've gotta get back to my place.
It's in the firing line of that.

06:38.160 --> 06:40.520
You understand?
Mm-hm.

06:40.520 --> 06:43.720
Do you wanna come with me?
OK.

06:43.720 --> 06:46.040
Alright, well, we gotta move.
So let's go.

06:47.040 --> 06:48.920
The dog, he's Boss.

06:48.920 --> 06:50.680
Come on. Boss! (WHISTLES)

06:50.680 --> 06:53.640
I'm Doug. What's your name?
Adut.

06:53.640 --> 06:55.240
What?
Adut.

06:55.240 --> 06:58.400
Adut?
Like Adut Akech, the model.

06:58.400 --> 06:59.640
Right, that's great.

06:59.640 --> 07:03.320
So you wanna be a model, do ya?
Nah, I wanna be an engineer.

07:04.560 --> 07:07.880
MADIT: Adut! Adut!

07:07.880 --> 07:09.520
MAN: Listen to instructions.

07:09.520 --> 07:12.320
(CHATTER AND LAUGHTER)

07:12.320 --> 07:15.000
This way, guys.
We're running out of time.

07:15.000 --> 07:16.960
Adut!

07:25.600 --> 07:28.480
(BABY CRIES)
(MADIT SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

07:32.480 --> 07:34.520
Adut!

07:35.800 --> 07:37.480
Adut!

07:41.840 --> 07:44.200
Excuse me,
I'm looking for my daughter.

07:44.200 --> 07:46.480
She's 10 years old.
She's about this tall.

07:46.480 --> 07:49.400
I haven't seen her, no. Sorry.

07:50.440 --> 07:52.680
Zac, just relax.
Sorry.

07:54.240 --> 07:56.640
Excuse me,
I'm looking for my daughter.

07:56.640 --> 07:59.040
She's 10 years old.
She's about this tall.

07:59.040 --> 08:01.560
DOUG: Her parents have gotta be here
somewhere, OK?

08:01.560 --> 08:03.760
She's not my kid.

08:03.760 --> 08:05.640
I can't stay with her, alright?

08:05.640 --> 08:07.120
I've got my place,
my tools, workshop.

08:07.120 --> 08:09.800
I've gotta go and protect that.
Some help, please? Please, someone!

08:09.800 --> 08:11.000
One minute.
Can someone...

08:11.000 --> 08:13.560
Wait!
..help my wife, please?

08:13.560 --> 08:15.280
(INDISTINCT RADIO COMMUNICATION)

08:16.560 --> 08:20.240
Look, you stay here, alright?
It's safe here, OK?

08:20.240 --> 08:24.600
Someone will...they'll...they'll come
and sort you out soon, OK?

08:24.600 --> 08:26.480
No, no, no, no. You stay.

08:26.480 --> 08:28.040
Just stay there.

08:28.040 --> 08:30.600
(PEOPLE CHATTER,
RADIO COMMUNICATION CONTINUES)

08:33.280 --> 08:35.360
MAN: Keep moving through.

08:43.160 --> 08:47.280
MAN ON RADIO: The fire front is
continuing to move towards town

08:47.280 --> 08:49.040
and some houses on the outskirts

08:49.040 --> 08:51.680
have unfortunately
already been lost.

08:51.680 --> 08:53.120
MADIT: I'm looking for my daughter.

08:53.120 --> 08:54.760
She's about 10 years old
and this tall.

08:54.760 --> 08:56.400
Have you guys seen her?
MAN: Sorry, mate.

08:56.400 --> 08:58.280
Madit.

09:00.120 --> 09:02.720
I cannot find her.
I wanna sit down.

09:02.720 --> 09:04.680
We're looking for your sister.

09:08.920 --> 09:10.400
MAN ON RADIO: I can't stress enough

09:10.400 --> 09:13.520
the importance of staying tuned
for updates.

09:13.520 --> 09:18.480
A wind change has been forecast,
which will help,

09:18.480 --> 09:20.880
but we don't know
when that will happen.

09:20.880 --> 09:23.880
So the situation
remains unpredictable.

09:23.880 --> 09:25.280
Alright. Well, thank you,

09:25.280 --> 09:27.200
Incident Controller Farrelly
from the VFA.

09:27.200 --> 09:29.280
I'll let you go.
I know how busy you are.

09:29.280 --> 09:34.120
Oh! It looks like my replacement
is here.

09:34.120 --> 09:36.560
So I'll be leaving you
in their capable hands.

09:37.960 --> 09:39.440
Coming up to news time.

09:39.440 --> 09:43.440
Here's a word
from one of our sponsors.

09:44.560 --> 09:46.040
WOMAN: Looking for
something to do tonight?

09:46.040 --> 09:48.800
The RSL offers a restaurant and bar,

09:48.800 --> 09:50.440
community bus and nightly...

09:51.480 --> 09:53.280
CARIS: About time.

09:54.440 --> 09:56.520
(SIRENS WAIL)

09:57.560 --> 09:58.720
You.

09:58.720 --> 10:00.840
What do you want?

10:00.840 --> 10:02.240
We need to get a message out.

10:02.240 --> 10:04.560
My mum's in Wangaratta.
She's freaking out.

10:04.560 --> 10:08.280
You were talking to the VFA.
So you've got a phone that works.

10:08.280 --> 10:09.760
You want me to help you?

10:09.760 --> 10:11.880
After what you did?

10:11.880 --> 10:14.360
Only station volunteers
and invited guests

10:14.360 --> 10:15.560
are allowed into the studio.

10:15.560 --> 10:17.040
Can't help you.

10:22.040 --> 10:25.160
My mum says she's gonna drive here,
through the fires.

10:25.160 --> 10:27.880
She can't. The road is closed.

10:27.880 --> 10:29.160
That won't stop her.

10:29.160 --> 10:31.000
She's a major stress-head.

10:31.000 --> 10:33.880
Because of his disability
and everything.

10:34.880 --> 10:36.520
Please.

10:40.880 --> 10:42.720
One call. That's it.

10:44.400 --> 10:46.640
Not you!

10:46.640 --> 10:48.800
I'm his interpreter.

10:50.800 --> 10:52.280
(SIGHS) Alright.

10:53.280 --> 10:56.160
(WISTFUL MUSIC)

10:57.160 --> 11:00.480
Good boy. Hey. OK.

11:05.320 --> 11:07.480
What are you doing back here?

11:07.480 --> 11:09.240
My parents weren't at the tent.

11:09.240 --> 11:11.160
They won't know where to go
to find me.

11:11.160 --> 11:13.240
Well, have a look around, kid.

11:13.240 --> 11:15.160
Hey? Can you see 'em here?

11:15.160 --> 11:16.560
They're not with me.

11:16.560 --> 11:18.240
(P.A. SYSTEM BEEPS)

11:18.240 --> 11:21.520
MAN ON P.A.: This is an emergency
warning for evacuees.

11:21.520 --> 11:24.720
There is a large fire front
moving towards Kooryang...

11:24.720 --> 11:27.560
(CONTINUES SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

11:27.560 --> 11:29.840
You're a fuckin'
pain in the arse, kid.

11:29.840 --> 11:31.520
And you swear too much.

11:31.520 --> 11:33.600
(ANNOUNCEMENT CONTINUES
INDISTINCTLY)

11:34.600 --> 11:36.160
You're not my problem.

11:37.240 --> 11:38.760
(BARKS)
What?

11:38.760 --> 11:40.360
Shut up.

11:41.360 --> 11:42.880
Come on.

11:46.000 --> 11:47.760
WOMAN ON SPEAKERPHONE:
I can still come.

11:47.760 --> 11:50.600
I'll wait at the roadblock
till it opens.

11:50.600 --> 11:52.040
I can't just sit around.

11:52.040 --> 11:54.320
Don't touch anything.

11:55.360 --> 11:56.520
I'm stressed.

11:56.520 --> 11:58.760
We'll be OK, Aunty M.

11:58.760 --> 12:01.280
We'll be fine at the wharf
with Mum.

12:01.280 --> 12:03.080
It'll be fine.

12:03.080 --> 12:05.320
Yeah, it's cool. Really.

12:05.320 --> 12:07.840
It is far from cool, Barney.

12:07.840 --> 12:10.200
Your grandad is beside himself.

12:11.480 --> 12:13.000
Jai, don't sign this.

12:13.000 --> 12:14.000
Alright.

12:14.000 --> 12:15.640
He's all I've got, OK?

12:15.640 --> 12:18.920
Just stay safe.

12:18.920 --> 12:21.720
All of you.
We will.

12:21.720 --> 12:23.920
'Bye. (HANGS UP)

12:31.560 --> 12:33.040
Thanks. We're going to go...

12:33.040 --> 12:34.840
You really are a little shit.

12:34.840 --> 12:36.040
Aren't you?

12:37.280 --> 12:40.080
Can you understand what I'm saying?
No, I'm deaf.

12:41.080 --> 12:43.600
This cousin of yours.
Did you know he was a criminal?

12:43.600 --> 12:44.600
No.

12:44.600 --> 12:47.840
He tagged my front fence.
I'd only just had it painted.

12:47.840 --> 12:50.960
I saw you. Don't deny it.

12:50.960 --> 12:55.280
My husband was a sick man
when you vandalised our home.

12:55.280 --> 12:57.880
And I had to deal with that
in between going to the hospital.

12:57.880 --> 12:59.960
You kids, you go around,
you don't care.

12:59.960 --> 13:01.320
You just destroy things.

13:01.320 --> 13:03.920
You don't care about the people
left behind to clean it all up.

13:03.920 --> 13:06.160
Don't you walk away from me.
I want an apology.

13:06.160 --> 13:07.440
(SCOFFS)

13:07.440 --> 13:08.640
Piss off!

13:12.240 --> 13:13.800
I'm sorry.

13:14.800 --> 13:15.800
I'm sorry. I'm...

13:17.440 --> 13:19.200
I didn't mean...

13:19.200 --> 13:22.120
(SOLEMN MUSIC)
(OMINOUS RUMBLING)

13:23.120 --> 13:24.720
Oh.

13:34.880 --> 13:37.680
(CROWD MURMURS)

13:39.480 --> 13:42.480
It's alright, Zoe, it's OK.

13:42.480 --> 13:43.680
MAN: What's going on?

13:43.680 --> 13:46.760
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

13:51.320 --> 13:53.080
(RUMBLING)

14:01.760 --> 14:04.080
(CLANG!)
(ELECTRICITY BUZZES)

14:04.080 --> 14:06.720
(OMINOUS MUSIC)
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

14:09.440 --> 14:10.440
DOUG: Adut?

14:11.840 --> 14:14.760
Adut! Come on. Come on.

14:14.760 --> 14:17.080
It's not safe here.

14:17.080 --> 14:18.760
We're gonna go back
to my place, alright?

14:18.760 --> 14:20.520
Now, when we get there,

14:20.520 --> 14:22.400
you're gonna stay in this tinnie
with Boss, alright?

14:22.400 --> 14:24.160
Until I finish doing
what I gotta do.

14:24.160 --> 14:26.080
But what about my parents?
Hey?

14:26.080 --> 14:27.360
And my sister.
It's alright.

14:27.360 --> 14:30.240
We'll...we'll find them
once this passes. I promise ya.

14:30.240 --> 14:33.360
Mummy!
MAN: Don't panic.

14:33.360 --> 14:35.800
It's just smoke blocking the sun.

14:35.800 --> 14:39.120
Keep it up. No need to run.
Everything's OK. Just keep moving.

14:39.120 --> 14:40.880
Nice and steady, but keep moving.

14:40.880 --> 14:43.360
It's gonna be much safer
in the water.

14:43.360 --> 14:46.520
But I can't swim.

14:48.080 --> 14:49.480
(CHUCKLES)

14:49.480 --> 14:51.160
That's OK.

14:53.000 --> 14:54.320
Don't worry. Yep.

14:55.320 --> 14:58.240
I got something for ya, OK?

14:58.240 --> 15:00.200
Here, put your arms up.

15:02.280 --> 15:03.720
There.

15:03.720 --> 15:08.200
Now...this life jacket
is gonna be big for ya.

15:08.200 --> 15:11.000
So if this boat tips over,
which it's not going to,

15:11.000 --> 15:13.120
you're going to have to
hold on tight up here,

15:13.120 --> 15:15.520
so you don't slip out, alright?

15:15.520 --> 15:17.640
No, you'll be fine.

15:18.960 --> 15:21.120
(GRUNTS)

15:21.120 --> 15:23.720
Unless you need medical attention,
keep on moving, onto the wharf.

15:23.720 --> 15:25.800
And at the front of the wharf,
keep going down.

15:25.800 --> 15:27.680
We've got more people to come on.
Excuse me.

15:27.680 --> 15:29.560
We're looking for our daughter.
Sorry?

15:29.560 --> 15:31.080
My daughter. She's 10 years old.

15:31.080 --> 15:33.320
Ah, if she's here,
she'll be on the wharf.

15:33.320 --> 15:36.120
Please help us.
We've already looked there.

15:36.120 --> 15:39.200
Everyone's down there.
Come on, guys, keep moving.

15:39.200 --> 15:41.120
Look, there's nowhere else
she could be.

15:41.120 --> 15:42.520
Adut!
We've evacuated the area.

15:42.520 --> 15:44.840
Adut!
MADIT: Adut! Adut!

15:44.840 --> 15:46.520
(MOTOR HUMS)

15:57.600 --> 16:00.600
(FOREBODING MUSIC)

16:23.520 --> 16:26.960
I've just spoken to the VFA

16:26.960 --> 16:28.720
and they inform me that

16:28.720 --> 16:32.840
there's a large pyrocumulus cloud
formed by the fire,

16:32.840 --> 16:34.160
it's starting to bend

16:34.160 --> 16:36.080
and it is actually leaning over us.

16:36.080 --> 16:38.000
That's what's cutting out the light.

16:38.000 --> 16:39.400
There's no reason to panic,

16:39.400 --> 16:41.680
but there will be ash

16:41.680 --> 16:44.320
and embers in the cloud,

16:44.320 --> 16:46.880
so we need to keep
following instruction...

16:48.120 --> 16:51.160
No. (CLICKS BUTTONS)

16:51.160 --> 16:52.600
No.

16:54.480 --> 16:55.960
(GRUNTS)

16:55.960 --> 16:57.760
Oh, God, that's it. That's it.

16:57.760 --> 17:00.400
Goddammit.
I've gotta get back on air.

17:00.400 --> 17:01.960
Have you got a generator?

17:01.960 --> 17:03.800
A what?!
A generator.

17:03.800 --> 17:05.200
They should...they should have one.

17:05.200 --> 17:07.840
Well, I...I don't know.
I don't remember where it is.

17:07.840 --> 17:09.760
Do you know
where the power board is?

17:10.760 --> 17:13.240
Ah...out the back.

17:13.240 --> 17:14.880
Out the back maybe.

17:15.880 --> 17:17.480
Show me.

17:17.480 --> 17:19.400
(SIGHS)

17:30.120 --> 17:31.920
I think it's just downstairs.

17:35.360 --> 17:37.760
(RUMBLING)

17:44.000 --> 17:47.040
MAN ON RADIO: We apologise for the
disruption to our transmission.

17:47.040 --> 17:49.640
Normal service will resume shortly.

17:51.640 --> 17:53.480
(COUGHING)

17:59.000 --> 18:02.120
We apologise for the disruption
to our transmission.

18:02.120 --> 18:04.400
Normal service will resume shortly.

18:04.400 --> 18:06.120
What's this, hey?

18:06.120 --> 18:08.640
It's an old-fashioned camp-out.

18:08.640 --> 18:10.600
You OK?
I'm good.

18:10.600 --> 18:12.120
Good. (KISSES)

18:13.120 --> 18:14.520
Where are the boys?

18:14.520 --> 18:16.520
They went to the radio station
to call your sister.

18:16.520 --> 18:18.960
Shit.
It was Jai's idea.

18:18.960 --> 18:21.080
(SIGHS) I'm gonna kill that kid.

18:23.360 --> 18:25.000
What's happening?

18:28.400 --> 18:32.440
The fire's hitting houses on the
outskirts of town. It's close.

18:33.440 --> 18:36.280
We apologise for the disruption
to our transmission.

18:36.280 --> 18:39.080
Normal service will resume shortly.
The radio station's brick.

18:39.080 --> 18:41.400
It's probably safer than here.

18:41.400 --> 18:42.880
Yeah.

18:44.880 --> 18:46.960
I gotta get back.
I've got a call-out.

18:46.960 --> 18:48.920
Don't go, Dad.

18:48.920 --> 18:51.760
It's OK, Ellsy.
Don't let him go.

18:51.760 --> 18:54.160
Please, Mum.
Nothing is gonna happen to me.

18:54.160 --> 18:56.160
We're all gonna be OK, alright?

18:56.160 --> 18:58.280
Right.

18:58.280 --> 19:00.160
I love you.

19:00.160 --> 19:02.200
MAN ON RADIO: ..disruption
to our transmission.

19:02.200 --> 19:05.360
Normal service will resume shortly.

19:05.360 --> 19:07.680
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

19:07.680 --> 19:09.680
(HELICOPTER WHIRRS)

19:25.160 --> 19:26.840
(PHONE RINGS)

19:38.240 --> 19:39.520
JAI: Hello?

19:39.520 --> 19:41.640
(STATIC BUZZ ON PHONE)

19:41.640 --> 19:43.960
Hello.
(STATIC)

19:43.960 --> 19:46.080
MAN ON PHONE: I need help!

19:46.080 --> 19:49.720
What?
Help me, please! I need help!

19:49.720 --> 19:52.400
(STATIC AND CRACKLING)

19:52.400 --> 19:54.520
Well, what do you want me...
(LINE DISCONNECTS)

19:55.680 --> 19:56.880
Hello?

19:57.880 --> 19:59.840
Hello?

19:59.840 --> 20:02.840
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

20:06.040 --> 20:09.360
(MOTOR GROWLS AND STOPS)

20:09.360 --> 20:11.000
DOUG: Right.

20:12.000 --> 20:14.200
(GRUNTS) OK. OK.

20:15.440 --> 20:16.800
OK.

20:17.920 --> 20:19.120
Now...

20:21.880 --> 20:24.320
Here. Adut.

20:25.880 --> 20:28.800
If it gets too smoky, you just
hold that in front of your mouth.

20:28.800 --> 20:31.320
Just like that.
Like that. Yeah, yeah.

20:31.320 --> 20:33.680
Hey, you stay, OK?
(BOSS PANTS)

20:33.680 --> 20:35.960
Look after him.
Don't let him follow me.

20:36.960 --> 20:39.280
I'll be back soon as I can. Stay!

20:46.920 --> 20:49.480
MAN ON RADIO: Apologies for the
disruption to our transmission.

20:49.480 --> 20:52.160
Normal service will resume shortly.

20:52.160 --> 20:54.040
(CLICKING)

20:56.280 --> 20:58.040
(MACHINE BEEPS)

21:05.880 --> 21:09.320
Alright. Let's get this thing going.

21:09.320 --> 21:10.640
(DOOR SHUTS)

21:10.640 --> 21:12.880
Guys, someone...
Oh, good Lord.

21:12.880 --> 21:15.320
I need to get back on the air now.

21:15.320 --> 21:17.360
Some...someone called.

21:17.360 --> 21:19.200
You need to reboot it.
A man.

21:19.200 --> 21:21.120
I can probably do it.
A man called.

21:21.120 --> 21:23.880
(PHONE RINGS)

21:23.880 --> 21:26.680
Hold, please.
An...answer the phone.

21:26.680 --> 21:29.080
Are you sure? This is very
sophisticated equipment...

21:29.080 --> 21:31.640
Please. Please, guys, I'm serious.
It's a base model mixing console.

21:31.640 --> 21:33.080
I can do it.
Alright, go ahead.

21:33.080 --> 21:35.280
Answer the fucking phone!

21:35.280 --> 21:37.920
(PHONE BEEPS)
Hello?

21:37.920 --> 21:40.800
(STATIC)
MAN ON PHONE: Hello.

21:41.800 --> 21:44.080
I'm in my car.
I don't know which way to go.

21:44.080 --> 21:45.840
The fires are everywhere.

21:45.840 --> 21:48.360
Where are you?
Flinders Hill.

21:48.360 --> 21:51.200
Flinders Hill? That's miles away.
I left the house.

21:51.200 --> 21:54.280
I shouldn't have.
But the fire was right at the back.

21:55.760 --> 21:58.800
I came down Gordon's Road.
I should have taken a right.

21:58.800 --> 22:02.560
But I couldn't see and now
I don't know how far I've gone.

22:02.560 --> 22:05.120
We're...we're gonna get you help, OK?
Please!

22:05.120 --> 22:06.560
We're gonna help you.

22:07.680 --> 22:11.040
Alright, tell us where you are and
I can get the VFA to come to you.

22:11.040 --> 22:13.400
You said Gordon's Road? Whereabouts?

22:13.400 --> 22:16.520
I passed Lock Street,
I'm sure it was.

22:16.520 --> 22:19.880
Are you heading east or west?
East.

22:19.880 --> 22:22.120
No, west.

22:22.120 --> 22:23.880
I don't know.

22:23.880 --> 22:26.520
I can't see. It's so dark.

22:26.520 --> 22:28.120
It's going to be OK.

22:28.120 --> 22:31.600
You're gonna be alright.
I don't think I can see it.

22:31.600 --> 22:33.800
Look, I can get the fire brigade
to come to you

22:33.800 --> 22:36.320
but you need to tell me
exactly where you are.

22:36.320 --> 22:38.520
I don't know!

22:38.520 --> 22:39.920
No, listen. Listen to me.

22:39.920 --> 22:42.600
I need you to stop and think.

22:42.600 --> 22:45.200
East or west?
I couldn't see him.

22:45.200 --> 22:49.160
(STATIC)
It's so loud.

22:50.240 --> 22:53.560
Help me.
I don't know what is happening.

22:53.560 --> 22:56.840
Help me. Help...
(WHOOSH, LINE DISCONNECTS)

23:11.960 --> 23:14.440
Barney, we need to find Dad.
He can help.

23:21.360 --> 23:24.240
I'll call the VFA. He'll find him.
(DOOR SHUTS)

23:28.920 --> 23:31.160
Answer the goddamn phone.

23:31.160 --> 23:33.640
(GRUNTS AND COUGHS)

23:39.120 --> 23:40.680
(COUGHS)

23:48.400 --> 23:50.600
(RUMBLING CONTINUES)

24:03.440 --> 24:05.680
Come on. Come on.
(MOTOR FALSE STARTS)

24:07.680 --> 24:09.680
Fucker.

24:15.400 --> 24:17.440
Ahh! (GRUNTS)

24:21.440 --> 24:23.080
Come on.

24:24.080 --> 24:25.760
(GRUNTS)

24:34.040 --> 24:35.680
Fuck off!

24:37.200 --> 24:39.640
JAI: Dad!
(MAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY ON RADIO)

24:39.640 --> 24:41.520
Jai, Jesus!

24:41.520 --> 24:43.160
What do you think you're doing?
Flinders Hill.

24:43.160 --> 24:45.160
You have to go there.
A man phoned the station.

24:45.160 --> 24:46.920
He's caught in the fire.
Where's Barney?

24:46.920 --> 24:48.600
The radio station. The man, Dad.

24:48.600 --> 24:51.480
Gordon's Road, near Lock Road.
He's there now. Come on.

24:51.480 --> 24:53.440
Jai, listen.
He's...he's in his car.

24:53.440 --> 24:56.240
I told him I'd get help. We can't
just stay here and do nothing...

24:56.240 --> 24:59.400
Jai! I can't go to Flinders Hill.

24:59.400 --> 25:01.760
OK? Our job is here now.

25:01.760 --> 25:04.320
Protecting the town.

25:04.320 --> 25:06.160
Flinders Hill is gone.

25:06.160 --> 25:08.320
(INDISTINCT RADIO COMMUNICATION)

25:09.320 --> 25:11.240
I'm sorry, son.

25:11.240 --> 25:13.560
We gotta go now, Raf.

25:15.160 --> 25:16.760
(SIGHS)

25:16.760 --> 25:18.400
Barney will be OK at the station,

25:18.400 --> 25:21.720
but you need to go to the wharf.

25:22.920 --> 25:24.440
Dad.

25:27.120 --> 25:28.840
(TYPES ON KEYBOARD)

25:31.760 --> 25:33.640
(SIGHS)

25:34.680 --> 25:36.760
Oh, gosh.

25:36.760 --> 25:38.040
Oh.

25:45.440 --> 25:47.000
Ah, we're back.

25:47.000 --> 25:49.080
Um, apologies for the hiccup.

25:49.080 --> 25:52.680
As you're probably aware,
we've lost power

25:52.680 --> 25:56.320
and I have an urgent update
from the VFA.

25:56.320 --> 25:59.040
The fire has reached
the edge of town.

26:00.040 --> 26:01.880
VFA trucks are falling back

26:01.880 --> 26:05.280
and will surround
the designated safer places

26:05.280 --> 26:07.880
as a last line of defence.

26:07.880 --> 26:09.800
If you hear the sirens,

26:09.800 --> 26:12.520
you must take immediate steps
to protect yourself.

26:12.520 --> 26:15.000
What does that mean?
Do we have to go in the water?

26:15.000 --> 26:17.000
I can't do that.
Here.

26:17.000 --> 26:19.600
Take off your shoes, hon.
We might have to go for a swim.

26:19.600 --> 26:21.760
I don't wanna swim.
It's OK. Come on.

26:21.760 --> 26:23.360
Come on, buddy, get up.

26:26.760 --> 26:28.280
CARIS ON RADIO: Hold on, everyone.

26:28.280 --> 26:29.880
ADUT: Boss, stay here.

26:29.880 --> 26:31.720
CARIS: And good luck.

26:32.920 --> 26:34.840
(BOSS BARKS)

26:47.520 --> 26:49.360
(CARIS SIGHS)

27:04.800 --> 27:09.240
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

27:09.240 --> 27:10.520
Jai.
Jai.

27:10.520 --> 27:12.760
Oh, thank God you're here.

27:14.920 --> 27:17.040
Where's Barney?

27:17.040 --> 27:18.640
He's at the radio station.

27:18.640 --> 27:21.000
Well, is he OK?

27:21.000 --> 27:23.760
Yeah, he's fine. He's fine.

27:25.800 --> 27:28.800
It's OK. Come here.
(LOUD RUMBLING)

27:28.800 --> 27:31.160
(FOREBODING MUSIC)

27:31.160 --> 27:33.440
(DISTANT BOOMS)

27:38.000 --> 27:40.400
(LOUD BOOMS)

27:41.560 --> 27:43.520
(HELICOPTER WHIRRS)

27:49.440 --> 27:52.240
(BANG!)
(CROWD EXCLAIMS)

27:53.240 --> 27:55.280
Madit.

27:56.280 --> 27:57.680
(SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

27:57.680 --> 27:59.160
Madit.

28:07.240 --> 28:08.960
(SIREN WAILS)

28:08.960 --> 28:10.840
You're safe.

28:12.480 --> 28:14.720
Your family is here.

28:16.720 --> 28:18.000
(SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

28:23.640 --> 28:25.360
(SIZZLES)

28:33.320 --> 28:35.840
(LOUD EXPLOSION, RUMBLING)

28:41.040 --> 28:42.080
Doug?

28:42.080 --> 28:43.840
DOUG: No!

28:45.400 --> 28:47.040
(GRUNTS)

28:48.800 --> 28:50.040
Fuck!

29:00.880 --> 29:01.880
(GRUNTS)

29:04.520 --> 29:06.520
Fuck!

29:08.160 --> 29:10.360
Come on, fucker!

29:13.440 --> 29:16.600
Doug!
(BOSS BARKS AND WHIMPERS)

29:16.600 --> 29:18.560
No, Boss.

29:19.560 --> 29:22.360
No! Boss, no! Boss, come back!

29:22.360 --> 29:24.520
(TENSE MUSIC)

29:34.360 --> 29:35.840
(WHISTLES)

29:35.840 --> 29:37.040
Boss!

29:37.040 --> 29:38.800
Boss!
Doug, I'm sorry!

29:38.800 --> 29:40.480
Hey! What are you doing here?

29:40.480 --> 29:42.560
I told you to stay on the boat
with Boss.

29:42.560 --> 29:43.680
He got out.

29:43.680 --> 29:45.360
You were supposed to keep hold
of him.

29:45.360 --> 29:46.360
I couldn't!

29:47.760 --> 29:49.760
I can't look after you, kid.

29:49.760 --> 29:52.800
You understand that?
I can't look after ya!

30:00.040 --> 30:01.520
Oh! Look out!

30:01.520 --> 30:03.600
(WIND HOWLS, FLAMES CRACKLE)

30:06.840 --> 30:09.840
(WISTFUL MUSIC)

30:25.920 --> 30:28.200
Boss. (WHISTLES)

30:28.200 --> 30:31.200
Come on. Come on.

30:31.200 --> 30:33.200
Let's get back to the boat. Come on.

30:33.200 --> 30:36.560
Start running. Come on.
Let's go. Let's go.

30:37.920 --> 30:39.640
(WAVES LAP)

30:42.960 --> 30:45.400
(DISTANT RUMBLING)

30:49.880 --> 30:52.440
(WIND HOWLS)

30:52.440 --> 30:54.760
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

30:59.720 --> 31:02.720
ELLSY: What is it?
I don't know.

31:13.440 --> 31:15.160
(MOTOR HUMS)

31:18.480 --> 31:20.400
(MOTOR STOPS)

31:28.480 --> 31:30.120
(BOOMING SOUNDS)

31:30.120 --> 31:32.320
(EXPLOSIONS)

31:34.360 --> 31:37.360
(WISTFUL MUSIC)

31:39.760 --> 31:42.400
(CRACKLING)

31:51.080 --> 31:53.280
Nope. No.

31:57.920 --> 32:00.920
MAN ON RADIO: The wind change
has pushed the fire away from town

32:00.920 --> 32:03.560
and back onto sections
which have already burned.

32:03.560 --> 32:06.720
There's no fuel load left so the
fire's starting to burn itself out.

32:06.720 --> 32:08.360
Sorry, just...
That's fine.

32:08.360 --> 32:12.680
To be absolutely clear,
are we safe?

32:12.680 --> 32:15.800
The emergency warning
is no longer in place.

32:15.800 --> 32:18.480
The immediate danger has passed.

32:20.840 --> 32:23.160
Thank you,
Incident Controller Farrelly.

32:23.160 --> 32:24.280
Right.

32:25.440 --> 32:28.440
We're OK. Thank God.

32:31.320 --> 32:36.320
You heard the man. The immediate
danger has passed. We're safe.

32:36.320 --> 32:39.360
(WHOOPING AND CHEERING)

33:12.360 --> 33:14.160
Thanks, mate.

33:15.680 --> 33:17.040
Yeah.

33:22.080 --> 33:24.960
How about we get you back
to your parents, huh?

33:26.600 --> 33:28.000
Yeah.

33:32.800 --> 33:39.800
SONG ON RADIO: # Should old
acquaintance be forgot... #

33:39.800 --> 33:41.920
I know it's early...

33:41.920 --> 33:43.920
# And never brought to... #

33:43.920 --> 33:46.720
..but Happy New Year, everyone.

33:46.720 --> 33:50.880
# Should old acquaintance... #

33:50.880 --> 33:53.680
Ooooh!
# Be forgot... #

33:53.680 --> 33:56.160
You know, God didn't have anything
to do with it, don't you?

33:56.160 --> 34:00.360
# Lang syne

34:00.360 --> 34:02.400
# For auld... #

34:02.400 --> 34:04.520
(BOTH LAUGH)

34:04.520 --> 34:07.600
# Lang syne, my dear

34:07.600 --> 34:12.760
# For auld lang syne

34:14.320 --> 34:17.560
# We'll take a cup

34:17.560 --> 34:21.360
# Of kindness yet

34:21.360 --> 34:26.800
# For auld lang syne

34:27.800 --> 34:32.240
# We too have paddled

34:32.240 --> 34:35.240
# In the brook

34:35.240 --> 34:36.320
# From morn... #

34:36.320 --> 34:38.160
Baba? Mama?

34:38.160 --> 34:40.240
MAMA: Adut!
MADIT: Adut!

34:42.400 --> 34:44.960
(SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE) Adut.
We were so worried!

34:46.240 --> 34:48.000
Are you OK?
You alright?

34:48.000 --> 34:49.440
What happened?
(SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

34:49.440 --> 34:51.600
A man helped me. He's got a dog.

34:51.600 --> 34:53.040
What man?
Where is he?

34:53.040 --> 34:54.280
He's over...

34:55.320 --> 35:00.880
# For auld lang syne

35:00.880 --> 35:02.120
# My dear

35:02.120 --> 35:07.840
# For auld lang syne

35:08.840 --> 35:12.680
# We'll take a cup

35:12.680 --> 35:16.200
# Of kindness yet

35:16.200 --> 35:22.200
# For auld lang syne. #

35:22.200 --> 35:23.880
(RAIN PATTERS)

35:33.240 --> 35:35.080
DOUG: Alright, go.

35:46.840 --> 35:48.440
(SIGHS)

35:51.560 --> 35:53.520
(UNZIPS)

35:53.520 --> 35:55.200
(PEES)

36:00.480 --> 36:02.120
(SIGHS)

36:02.120 --> 36:04.120
(IGNITION SWITCH CLICKS REPEATEDLY)

36:09.400 --> 36:12.360
Brekky. Here, here. Here you go.

36:14.440 --> 36:17.640
Here you go. Up, up, up.

36:26.240 --> 36:29.240
NEWSREADER: Thousands of homes
in New South Wales and Victoria

36:29.240 --> 36:30.600
are still without power

36:30.600 --> 36:34.120
after storms brought heavy rain
and flash flooding

36:34.120 --> 36:37.280
to a number of towns and regions
in yet another...

36:37.280 --> 36:39.560
RAF: Come on, mate. School.
..extreme weather event.

36:39.560 --> 36:41.920
Only a short time ago,
these same areas...

36:41.920 --> 36:42.920
Jai. School.

36:42.920 --> 36:45.360
..were threatened by the bushfires
that raged through the nation.

36:45.360 --> 36:46.440
Come on.

36:46.440 --> 36:49.520
People who had only just begun
cleaning up after the fires

36:49.520 --> 36:52.160
are now facing a clean-up
after the floods.

36:53.240 --> 36:55.040
A low-pressure cell...
(DOOR OPENS)

36:55.040 --> 36:57.240
..continues to move across...
(DOOR SHUTS)

36:57.240 --> 37:01.040
..the whole region and the bad news
is there's still more rain...

37:02.040 --> 37:04.440
(LAID-BACK BLUES PLAYS)

37:12.400 --> 37:16.520
SONG: # Chasing away the snakes
in a day

37:16.520 --> 37:20.520
# Run into trees and shrubs in a day

37:20.520 --> 37:22.600
# She tried to leave my house... #

37:22.600 --> 37:24.600
I'm Caris Mazzeo.

37:24.600 --> 37:26.000
And if you've just joined us,

37:26.000 --> 37:28.040
this is my new show,
The Listening Hour,

37:28.040 --> 37:30.440
and we've got one of our regulars,
Graham, on the line.

37:30.440 --> 37:31.880
How are you, my dear?

37:31.880 --> 37:36.840
GRAHAM ON RADIO: Oh, you know.
Keeping on.

37:36.840 --> 37:39.000
Still having the dreams, though.
Ah, the dreams.

37:39.000 --> 37:40.520
BOY: Jai!
Well, tell us about it.

37:40.520 --> 37:41.920
Hey, Jai, come see this!

37:41.920 --> 37:45.800
The fire's there and I'm ready
to fight, but I'm...I'm stuck.

37:46.840 --> 37:48.680
Jai!
My...my feet don't work.

37:48.680 --> 37:51.680
Bro, what's up?

37:51.680 --> 37:53.680
What are you doing, bro?
I can't move.

37:53.680 --> 37:56.160
What's wrong with me?

37:56.160 --> 37:57.600
Take your time, Graham.

38:00.520 --> 38:03.640
I just want to not smell that smell
anymore.

38:03.640 --> 38:05.440
The smoke...

38:06.680 --> 38:08.840
..got into everything.

38:08.840 --> 38:10.920
(SWITCHES STATION)

38:10.920 --> 38:13.760
(SLOW MOODY ROCK MUSIC)

38:21.560 --> 38:23.400
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

38:26.200 --> 38:28.400
Not again.
(KNOCKING)

38:29.600 --> 38:31.640
I don't need any help.

38:32.640 --> 38:34.240
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

38:37.440 --> 38:38.720
(GRUNTS)

38:49.560 --> 38:51.400
(DOUG MUTTERS)

38:55.040 --> 38:57.720
I haven't even got a dry chair
to offer you.

38:57.720 --> 38:59.240
That's fine.

39:00.840 --> 39:03.280
A cup of tea?
No, that's OK.

39:03.280 --> 39:04.800
It's all I got. (CHUCKLES)

39:04.800 --> 39:08.400
I applied for...temporary housing.

39:08.400 --> 39:09.960
(CLICKS SWITCH)

39:09.960 --> 39:13.920
They offered me some sort of pod,
like I'm a friggin' dolphin.

39:13.920 --> 39:14.960
(LAUGHS)

