40:09.640 --> 40:11.520
So you can build a new home.

40:16.240 --> 40:18.000
Uh...uh...

40:23.040 --> 40:24.520
Thanks.

40:31.440 --> 40:34.440
I'm talking with Andrew,
who's telling us

40:34.440 --> 40:37.360
how he and his family
are bringing life back to their land

40:37.360 --> 40:38.960
after the fires.

40:38.960 --> 40:40.280
That's right.

40:40.280 --> 40:44.560
Uh, as I was saying, the first thing
we did was go out to country,

40:44.560 --> 40:46.520
put out water stations and molasses

40:46.520 --> 40:48.800
to draw in the ants and the bees.

40:48.800 --> 40:50.240
The pollinators.

40:50.240 --> 40:54.760
From the insects, the cycle
just builds with bigger things.

40:54.760 --> 40:57.920
Birds, animals come in.

40:57.920 --> 41:01.360
And seeing them all come back,
we all have smiles on our faces.

41:01.360 --> 41:04.200
We're that stoked.
Mm-hm.

41:04.200 --> 41:06.360
We're the custodians of the land,
you know.

41:06.360 --> 41:08.880
We should we looking after it,

41:08.880 --> 41:10.600
but that link got broken.

41:10.600 --> 41:14.080
Do you think that it's too late
to fix it?

41:17.800 --> 41:20.720
I think, 'cause of the fires,

41:20.720 --> 41:22.680
uh, everyone feels
a part of this now.

41:22.680 --> 41:24.840
So I say to people...

41:25.880 --> 41:29.920
..go outside, into the bush,
paddock, whatever...

41:31.040 --> 41:32.960
..and just listen.

41:32.960 --> 41:36.080
Something will catch your ear
or your eye...

41:36.080 --> 41:37.080
Yeah.

41:37.080 --> 41:39.560
..that just connects with you

41:39.560 --> 41:43.080
and makes you feel like
you have to look after it.

41:44.200 --> 41:46.040
That's how we'll fix things.

